    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Before you start cooking, take your <strong>steak</strong> out of the fridge, open the packet and let it adjust to room temperature</p><p>Boil a kettle, then peel and chop your <strong>potato[es]</strong> into bite-sized pieces</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped potato</strong> to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> over a high heat and bring to the boil</p><p>Cook for 10-15 min or until fork-tender</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/salsa-macha-steak-with-loaded-black-bean-and-sweet-potato-mash/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once done, drain, return them to the pot and cover to keep warm</p><p>Add a small knob of <strong>butter</strong> and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> to the <strong>warmed potatoes</strong> and mash them until smooth</p><p>Tip: If the mash has cooled down, warm it through over a low heat, stirring constantly</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/salsa-macha-steak-with-loaded-black-bean-and-sweet-potato-mash/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, bash the <strong>pumpkin seeds</strong> in their bag with a <strong>rolling pin</strong></p><p>Heat a large, dry wide-based pan over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>bashed pumpkin seeds</strong> and <strong>sesame seeds</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and cook for 2-3 min or until toasted and lightly golden</p><p>Tip: Watch them like a hawk to make sure they don't burn!</p><p>Reserve the pan</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/salsa-macha-steak-with-loaded-black-bean-and-sweet-potato-mash/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Cut your <strong>lime[s]</strong> in half</p><p>Combine the<strong> toasted pumpkin seeds</strong>, <strong>toasted sesame seeds</strong>,<strong> soy sauce </strong>and<strong> chipotle paste</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) in a small bowl</p><p>Add a squeeze of <strong>lime juice</strong>,<strong> </strong>a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong>,<strong> </strong>1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp] </span><strong>olive oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>sugar</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up \u2013 this is your <strong>DIY salsa macha</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/salsa-macha-steak-with-loaded-black-bean-and-sweet-potato-mash/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Trim, then chop your <strong>spring onion[s]</strong> finely</p><p>Chop your<strong> coriander </strong>finely, including the stalks</p><p>Drain and rinse your <strong>black beans</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/salsa-macha-steak-with-loaded-black-bean-and-sweet-potato-mash/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat the reserved pan over a high heat</p><p>Pat your<strong> rump steak[s]</strong> dry with kitchen paper, then drizzle them with a little <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> on both sides</p><p>Once very hot, add the<strong> rump steak[s] </strong>to the pan</p><p>For rare, cook for 2-3 min max on each side; for medium-rare, cook for 3-4 min on each side; for medium, cook for 4-5 min on each side</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/salsa-macha-steak-with-loaded-black-bean-and-sweet-potato-mash/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the steaks are cooked, transfer to a plate to rest</p><p>While the steaks are resting, return the reserved pan to a medium-high heat with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>drained black beans</strong> with a pinch of<strong> salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> and cook for 2-3 min or until your beans are warmed through</p><p>Slice the <strong>rested steak</strong> finely on a clean board</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/salsa-macha-steak-with-loaded-black-bean-and-sweet-potato-mash/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Cut the <strong>remaining lime</strong> into wedges</p><p>Serve the <strong>potato mash</strong> topped with the <strong>sliced spring onion</strong>, <strong>toasted black beans</strong> and <strong>chopped coriander</strong></p><p>Serve the <strong>sliced steak</strong> to the side with the<strong> DIY salsa macha</strong> drizzled over the top</p><p>Garnish with a<strong> lime wedge</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
